@nhathaway, for your specific use case: if you use the Nginx plugin, it assumes that you want to use Nginx to authorize every domain contained in the cert. `--allow-subset-of-names`, if it didn't error out, would just drop the mail subdomain from the cert and successfully renew with the remainder of the domains.

I would recommend getting two different certs, one just for the mail that's renewed using standalone, and one with every subdomain that you use within Nginx.

It's hard for us to generically add functionality to authorize a domain that Nginx doesn't know about at all (where there's no server block that could possibly match that subdomain), because we use your server settings like port number to know how we should talk to that specific subdomain.

@kesar The API listen address defaults to `127.0.0.1:5001` which shows up as being used by `ipfs` in your `lsof ` output. 

However you are quite correct that the error message is highly confusing.
Thanks for bringing this to our attention.

